IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Group of health centers serving northern Maine. Five of the centers have FQHC designation.
IRS990.MissionDescription: Multi-specialty outpatient healthcare organization, promoting the development of quality health care, health care services and the development and operation of related activities necessary to encourage quality health care in Aroostook County.
IRS990.Description: Family Practice Services provide general care to families. The services are performed by physicians, physician assistants, and family nurse practitioners. This service has been provided since the date of inception.

Activity2.Description: Internal Medicine Services provide internal medicine to patients with more severe medical complications. The services are performed by physicians. This service has been provided since the date of inception.

Activity3.Description: Obstetrical and gynecological services are provided to female patients. These services are performed by physicians & Certified Nurse Midwives. This service has been provided since the date of inception.

ActivityOther.Description: Various other medical services provided to patients.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Pines Health Services has its Form 990 reviewed by the board prior to filing. The 990 is given to the CEO for review and forwarded to the Board of Directors to be discussed at a regularly scheduled Board of Directors meeting. If a meeting cannot be held prior to the submission deadline, the Organization forwards the 990 electronically to the Board of Directors for review and comment.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Annually, the Board of Directors sign forms indicating there are no conflicts of interest. If a conflict is brought to the board's attention, appropriate action will take place depending on the situation. This includes not allowing the member to vote on issues where there is a conflict, or other actions deemed necessary and appropriate by the board.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: For executives, the Board Executive Committee will review local market conditions and other factors. The salary is set below the MGMA national median range for practices of comparable size group by number of physicians, revenues and number of employees. For key employees (physicians, mid level providers), salary is set based on the MGMA annual Physician Compensation & Productivity Survey.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Organization makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy, and financial statements available to the public upon request.
This audit process has not changed from prior years.
Prior year numbers have been restated to present revenue net of contractual and charity care adjustments.
